+### 3.83 FR-E83: Journal Snapshots and Crash-Safe Compaction [ANC:fr:e83]
+
+- **Description:** Bound durable journal replay cost by allowing
+  `journal.jsonl` to contain `state_snapshot` events and by providing a
+  crash-safe compaction operation that rewrites a run journal to one snapshot
+  plus tail events without weakening FR-E69 recovery semantics.
+- **Tasks:** [REF:task:2026-06-journal-snapshots-compaction | journal-snapshots-compaction]
+- **Status:** [ ]
+- **Acceptance criteria:**
+  - `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::snapshot round-trip equivalence`:
+    snapshot plus tail replay is byte-equal to full replay JSON, old
+    no-snapshot journals replay unchanged, and future snapshot versions fail
+    with journal path and version.
+  - `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::suffix-only compacted replay`:
+    compacted replay parses only the snapshot line plus subsequent tail and
+    retains torn-tail tolerance when the torn line follows a snapshot.
+  - `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::compaction crash injection`:
+    aborts between every adjacent compaction protocol step leave either the
+    old journal or the compacted journal replayable.
+  - `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::compaction refusal cases`:
+    compaction refuses live locked runs and unreplayable journals without
+    modifying the journal, tmp, or backup files.
+  - `src/config/config_test.ts::journal_compaction_threshold_events`:
+    settings-level threshold is a non-negative integer, defaults to a
+    documented non-zero value, `0` disables automatic compaction, and
+    workflow-only defaults do not leak into node settings.
+  - `src/engine/engine_test.ts::journal compaction threshold`: automatic
+    compaction runs only at node-completion boundaries after the threshold is
+    exceeded and emits one verbose status line.
+  - `src/cli_test.ts::runs compact`: manual CLI supports dry-run no-op, exact
+    success summary, help text, and one-line non-zero errors.
