+---
+date: "2026-06-12"
+status: done
+implements: [FR-E83]
+tags: [engine, recovery, journal, cli]
+related_tasks:
+  - 2026/05/durable-run-lifecycle-replay.md
+---
+# engine: Journal snapshots and crash-safe compaction
+
+## Goal
+
+Bound `journal.jsonl` replay cost without weakening the durable recovery
+contract by adding in-journal state snapshots and one crash-safe compaction
+operation shared by automatic engine execution and manual CLI use.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+FR-E69 made `<workflow>/runs/<run-id>/journal.jsonl` the authoritative
+append-only recovery stream. Long runs can now accumulate unbounded history,
+so every resume/replay pays the full prefix cost even when the prefix only
+reconstructs a state already known at a later point.
+
+### Current State
+
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts` is the single replay authority.
+- Replay starts from empty state, deduplicates event IDs, tolerates one torn
+  trailing line, and rejects malformed non-tail lines.
+- Engine lifecycle code appends bootstrap, node, attempt, loop, and terminal
+  events.
+- There is no snapshot event, no journal compaction API, no automatic
+  threshold, and no `runs compact` CLI command.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- Reuse `run-journal.ts`; do not add a second replayer.
+- Keep JSONL plain text; no compression or sidecar snapshot files.
+- Compaction protocol order is fixed: replay current journal, write tmp with
+  one snapshot and zero tail events, fsync tmp, copy current journal to bak,
+  atomically rename tmp over journal.
+- Refuse compaction when the run lock is held by a live process or replay
+  fails beyond standard torn-tail tolerance.
+- New config field is `defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events`; `0`
+  disables automatic compaction.
+- Engine auto-compaction may run only after node completion boundaries.
+- Benchmark override: no human variant gate. Selected variant recorded here.
+
+## Definition of Done
+
+- [x] FR-E83: Journal replay accepts `state_snapshot`, refuses unsupported
+      versions with journal path + version, and preserves old no-snapshot
+      replay. Test:
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::snapshot round-trip equivalence`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: Replay seeds from the latest valid snapshot, applies only the
+      suffix, proves compacted replay reads only snapshot plus tail, and keeps
+      torn-tail tolerance after a snapshot. Test:
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::suffix-only compacted replay`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: Shared compaction follows the required tmp/fsync/bak/rename
+      order, keeps one `journal.jsonl.bak`, and crash-injection points all
+      leave a replayable journal. Test:
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::compaction crash injection`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: Compaction refuses live locked runs and unreplayable journals
+      without modifying files. Test:
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::compaction refusal cases`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: `journal_compaction_threshold_events` is validated, defaulted,
+      drift-covered, and documented. Test:
+      `src/config/config_test.ts::journal_compaction_threshold_events`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: Engine triggers visible verbose compaction only at node
+      completion boundaries when events since snapshot exceed threshold.
+      Test: `src/engine/engine_test.ts::journal compaction threshold`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: `flowai-workflow runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <runId>
+      [--dry-run]` supports dry-run no-op, exact success summary, help text,
+      and one-line non-zero errors. Test:
+      `src/cli_test.ts::runs compact`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: SRS and SDS document the requirement, acceptance, snapshot event,
+      and compaction protocol. Test:
+      `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md::FR-E83`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: Full project gate passes. Test: `deno task check`; Evidence:
+      `deno task check`.
+
+## Solution
+
+### Selected Variant
+
+Architecturally-correct. Extend the existing journal replay and writer module
+with snapshot semantics and compaction helpers, then call the same helper from
+engine node-boundary integration and CLI. This avoids duplicate replay logic
+and keeps the durability boundary in one subsystem.
+
+Variant rationale:
+
+- Quick fix: rewrite `journal.jsonl` from current replay state only. Rejected
+  because it would likely bypass lock refusal, crash injection, CLI reuse, or
+  replay equivalence tests.
+- Architecturally-correct: add snapshot events and compaction inside
+  `run-journal.ts`, expose a small shared API, wire engine and CLI to it.
+  Selected because it satisfies all constraints with limited scope.
+- Best long-term: introduce pluggable journal storage and multi-generation
+  retention. Rejected because compression, batch compaction, and retention are
+  explicitly out of scope.
+
+### Files to Modify
+
+- `src/types.ts`
+  - Add `state_snapshot` event kind and payload fields:
+    `snapshot_version: 1`, `state: RunState`, `events_covered: number`.
+  - Add compaction result/stat types if useful for callers.
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts`
+  - Extend replay to find the latest supported snapshot, seed from its full
+    state, deduplicate/apply only subsequent events, and reject future snapshot
+    versions with a path-specific error.
+  - Add internal parse instrumentation option for suffix-only tests without
+    changing public behavior.
+  - Add `compactRunJournal(runDir, workflowDir?, opts?)` shared API:
+    check live lock, replay current journal, build one snapshot line, write
+    `journal.jsonl.tmp`, fsync and close tmp, copy journal to
+    `journal.jsonl.bak`, rename tmp over journal, and return before/after
+    events and bytes.
+  - Add dry-run stats helper that replays and reports event/byte counts
+    without writing.
+  - Add test-only crash hook after each protocol step.
+- `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts`
+  - Add snapshot equivalence, suffix-only, torn-tail, crash-injection, and
+    refusal tests.
+- `src/config/config.ts`, `src/types.ts`, config tests
+  - Add `defaults.journal_compaction_threshold_events`, default non-zero
+    value, and non-negative integer validation.
+  - Ensure it remains workflow-only and cannot leak into node settings.
+- `src/engine/engine.ts`, engine tests
+  - After successful node completion, call an engine helper that compacts only
+    when events since latest snapshot exceeds the threshold.
+  - Print one verbose status line when compaction runs.
+- `src/cli.ts`, CLI tests
+  - Add `runs compact` parser using existing argument style and no dependency.
+  - Resolve run directory from `--workflow` + `--run`, support `--dry-run`,
+    exact success summary, help text, and one-line errors.
+- `documents/requirements-engine.md`,
+  `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md`,
+  `documents/design-engine/04-data-and-logic.md`,
+  `documents/index.md`
+  - Register FR-E83 and document the recovery contract extension.
+
+### Error Handling
+
+- Unsupported snapshot versions throw `Unsupported journal snapshot version
+  at <journal path>: <version>`.
+- Any malformed non-tail record fails replay before compaction writes.
+- Live lock refusal throws a clear one-line error; CLI catches it and exits
+  non-zero without stack trace.
+- Crash hook errors intentionally abort at deterministic protocol points; tests
+  then replay the remaining journal on disk.
+
+### Verification Commands
+
+- `deno task check`
+- Focused during RED/GREEN:
+  `deno task test -- src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts`
+  `deno task test -- src/config/config_test.ts`
+  `deno task test -- src/engine/engine_test.ts`
+  `deno task test -- src/cli_test.ts`
+
+## Follow-ups
+
+- Multi-generation backup retention is intentionally out of scope.
+- Compression or binary journal encoding is intentionally out of scope.
+
+## Review Verdict
+
+Approve. The implementation satisfies FR-E83 requested behavior and constraints:
+snapshot replay equivalence, latest-snapshot suffix replay, torn-tail tolerance,
+crash-safe tmp/fsync/bak/rename compaction, live-lock and bad-journal refusal,
+node-completion-only automatic compaction, manual `runs compact`, and docs.
+Evidence: `deno task check` passed on 2026-06-12 with 1028 tests.
